lexUnit.name: fetch.v
lexUnit.definition: COD: go for and bring back.

sentence.text: He fetched water and splashed it over the twitching boy .
He fetched cold water in the saucepan , adding it to the hot water .
He fetched his sleeping bag from the cornbin , where he kept it so the mice would n't make a nest in it , and curled up to go to sleep .
So they fetched this poor innocent away from his family , across the sea , to a strange land .
Bridget had just fetched the vacuum cleaner .
He fetched a detector from his luggage .
He fetched a blanket from the bedroom and wrapped it round Doyle 's body , trying not to touch the wounds .
` This lady is fetching her kids from school .
I 'll fetch you a bigger one .
They had fetched him for Christmas and he was staying on for the New Year .
They fetched Celia from class , and Juliet felt guilty .
When he fetched me from hospital after my baby died , we drove home in the dark .
Chola fetched him some tobacco and a parcel of turmeric .
He was fetched from his home by Mr. Ted Warren , one of Dad 's old friends .
Now she fetched in the tray , and they all sat down .
